b'Student Health and Wellness'
b'Home'
b'Education'
b'MD Student Services and Support'
b'tlowery1'
b'Student Health\xc2\xa0and Wellness'
b'Student Health and Wellness at\xc2\xa0the UIC Health Sciences Campus-Rockford serves students registered in the College of Medicine, College of Pharmacy and College\xc2\xa0of Nursing programs at the\xc2\xa0Rockford campus.'
b'As part of tuition and fees each semester,\xc2\xa0students are charged a mandatory health service fee. The fee covers general operating costs for Student Health and Wellness, which provides medical services, counseling and wellness activities. Registered students have access to services covered by student health fees, regardless of their insurance coverage. If you require services beyond what is provided under student health fees, consult your insurance policy (CampusCare or private plans). Student Health and Wellness at UIC Health Sciences Campus\xe2\x80\x93Rockford accepts the majority of private insurance plans and can serve as\xc2\xa0a medical home\xc2\xa0for a student.'
b'CampusCare'
b'Health Services'
b'Student-Fee Covered:'
b'Private Insurance and CampusCare:'
b'Through Student Health and Wellness, students can obtain outside of the student fee'
b'Counseling Services'
b'Professional and confidential psychiatry and counseling services are offered to all UIC Health Sciences Campus-Rockford students.'
b'Students are eligible for 20 combined counseling or psychiatric services sessions at Student Health and Wellness for such issues as:'
b'Wellness Activities'
b'We provide health and wellness information sessions and educational programs, as well as knowledge and skill-building activities for our student communities that encourage healthy choices and lifestyles.'
b'Programming is available to all students. Topics may include:'
b'Hours'
b'Monday Health Services 8 a.m.-4 p.m. Counseling/Psychiatry 9 a.m.-1 p.m.'
b'Tuesday Health Services 8:30 a.m.-12:30 p.m. Counseling 8 a.m.-4 p.m.'
b'Wednesday Health Services 9 a.m.-7 p.m. Counseling/Psychiatry 3 p.m.-7 p.m.'
b'Thursday Health Services 8 a.m.-4 p.m. Counseling 8 a.m.-4 p.m.'
b'Friday Health Services 8 a.m.-Noon'
b'Location'
b'Student Health and Wellness is located in room N113 at the UIC Health Sciences Campus-Rockford, 1601 Parkview Ave., Rockford, Illinois, 61107.'
b'Appointments'
b'Call (815) 395-5870 to schedule an appointment.'
b'After hours:'
b'In the event that you have an acute illness and Student Health and Wellness services are unavailable, the following locations are available:'
b'Medical/MBT/Pharmacy/Nursing Students:'
b'MBT/Pharmacy/Nursing Students ONLY'
b'Staff'
b'Noel Pycior, MS, APRN, FNP-BC Family Nurse Practitioner Director of Student Health and Wellness'
b'Benjamin Shepherd, MD Psychiatrist'
b'Judith Heinschel, PhD, PMHNP-BC Mental Health Nurse Practitioner'
b'Anne Zuba, MSW, LCSW Student Health and Wellness Counselor'
b'In Crisis?'
b'Students are routinely scheduled for the next available appointment during business hours. A student in crisis may be scheduled for an emergency office visit by one of our providers as needed. If you feel you are experiencing a crisis, please do not hesitate to contact us. Call us as soon as possible at (815) 395-5870.'
b'After Hours'
b'If you are experiencing a crisis or emergency and require services outside of Student Health and Wellness\xe2\x80\x99s regular business hours, a number of resources are available to provide the support you need.'
b'In the event of a life-threatening mental health emergency for which you require immediate emergency services, regardless of insurance coverage or proximity to where your home is, please dial 911 or go to the closest emergency room to receive immediate care.'
b'If you believe that your concerns require immediate attention, but you do not feel that you need to be seen in person or require immediate emergency hospital care, please contact one of the crisis hotlines provided below for assistance:'
b'InTouch Crisis Hotline (312) 996-5535 Sunday-Friday 6 p.m.-10 p.m. The InTouch Hotline is a free crisis intervention, counseling and referral service offered to UIC students and members of the greater Chicagoland area. The InTouch Hotline is staffed by volunteers trained through the UIC Counseling Center Paraprofessional Program. Calls placed to the InTouch Hotline remain confidential and are treated in an objective, non-judgemental fashion.'
b'Alternatively, you may call these hotlines available 24/7:'
b'National Suicide Prevention Hotline (800) 273-8255'
b'Northwestern Memorial Hospital Outpatient Psychiatry Hotline (312) 926-8100'
b'Other Resources'
b'Visit the UIC Counseling Center\xe2\x80\x99s website for self-help resources.'
